</LG>
<LG>
<L>"Exalted MAN! forgive my wounded pride,</L>
<L>"Which &s;till its &s;ore chagrins would &s;eek to hide.</L>
<L>"O could&s;t thou think it?&mdash;yet, by Hell<NOTE N="&dagger;" PLACE="foot">Profanity&mdash;another characteri&s;tic of Ari&s;tocracy: this is the &s;e|cond time that ARISTUS has &s;worn by Hell. Profanity, I have been told, was deemed by him a de&s;irable accompli&s;hment: nay, I have &s;omewhere heard that he even thought it an e&s;&s;ential part of <HI>female</HI> education.</NOTE>, 'tis true&mdash;</L>
<L>"Cur&s;t be th'occa&s;ion, and the rival too!</L>
<L>"Yes&mdash;tho' as yet upon my chin appear'd</L>
<L>"But youthful down, my ardent &s;word I rear'd,</L>
<L><PB N="13" REF="028172_0011_0FD7356105B7DA18">
"And ru&s;h'd to combat in my country's cau&s;e;</L>
<L>"(For thus was call'd, my pa&s;&s;ion for applau&s;e&mdash;)</L>
<L>"Yet was I le&s;t, neglected, and alone,</L>
<L>"While HE, capricious Fortune's favour'd &s;on,</L>
<L>"Lo&s;t be the memory of his hated name!</L>
<L>"Who &s;till precedes me in the walks of fame;</L>
